tion, file, or line of code to understand _why_ it exists.\n    33\t\n    34\tCurrent behavior:\n    35\t\n    36\t- identifies the commit that introduced the code via git blame/log\n    37\t- reads the session transcript via `entire explain --no-pager --commit <sha>`\n    38\t- works with functions, files, and individual line changes\n    39\t- reports clearly when code is untracked, uncommitted, or created outside an Entire session\n    40\t\n    41\t### `what-happened`\n    42\t\n    43\tExplains what happened to a specific code block by tracing the latest change for a file range or pasted snippet through git blame and Entire checkpoints.\n    44\t\n    45\tCurrent behavior:\n    46\t\n    47\t- resolves file ranges or pasted snippets to exact line numbers\n    48\t- groups matching blame ranges by unique commit before reading checkpoint context\n    49\t- uses cheap-first `entire explain` lookups before expanding checkpoint transcripts\n    50\t- falls back to clearly labeled current-code analysis when checkpoint-backed context is unavailable\n    51\t\n    52\tExamples:\n    53\t\n    54\t- \"what happened here: `src/auth.ts:42-57`\"\n    55\t- \"what happened to this block?\" plus a pasted snippet\n    56\t\n    57\t### `search`\n    58\t\n    59\tSearches Entire checkpoint history and transcripts to find prior work by topic, repo, branch, author, or time window.\n    60\t\n    61\tCurrent behavior:\n    62\t\n    63\t- runs `entire search \"<query>\" --json` and summarizes the top matches\n    64\t- supports filters: `--repo`, `--branch`, `--author`, `--date`, and inline query filters like `author:<name>`, `date:week`\n    65\t- drills into a specific result with `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n    66\t- broadens searches progressively when initial results are empty (remove branch filter, widen date, simplify terms)\n    67\t\n    68\t## Installation\n    69\t\n    70\tInstall the agent that matches your workflow from its marketplace, manifest, or install-doc entrypoint:\n    71\t\n    72\t### Claude Code (via Plugin Marketplace)\n    73\t\n    74\tIn Claude Code, register the marketplace first:\n    75\t\n    76\t```bash\n    77\t/plugin marketplace add entireio/skills\n    78\t```\n    79\t\n    80\tThen install the plugin from this marketplace:\n    81\t\n    82\t```bash\n    83\t/plugin install entire \n    84\t```\n    85\t\n    86\t### Codex\n    87\t\n    88\tUse `plugins/entire/.codex-plugin/plugin.json`.\n    89\t\n    90\t### OpenCode\n    91\t\n    92\tUse the package-based flow in `.opencode/INSTALL.md`.\n    93\t\n    94\t### Cursor\n    95\t\n    96\tUse `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json`.\n    97\t\n    98\t### Gemini\n    99\t\n   100\t```bash\n   101\tgemini extensions install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n   102\t```\n   103\t\n   104\t## Quick Start\n   105\t\n   106\tNatural language examples:\n   107\t\n   108\t- \"hand off this session\"\n   109\t- \"hand off the codex session\"\n   110\t- \"pick up where codex left off\"\n   111\t- \"hand off checkpoint 7b7c2be8a262\"\n   112\t- `/explain parseConfig` — why does this function exist?\n   113\t- `/explain src/auth.ts` — what drove this file's creation?\n   114\t- \"search past work for rate limiting\"\n   115\t- \"find checkpoints about the migration\"\n   116\t- \"have we done this before?\"\n   117\t\n   118\t## Checkpoint Resolution\n   119\t\n   120\tCheckpoints are resolved in this order:\n   121\t\n   122\t1. local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch\n   123\t2. `.entire/settings.json` `checkpoint_remote`\n   124\t3. nearby local clone\n","exit_code":0,"duration":{"secs":0,"nanos":2084},"formatted_output":"","status":"completed"}}
